```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false;
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log == (int) log;
    }
}
```

This solution works because `Math.log(n) / Math.log(3)` will give you the exponent of 3 in the expression `3^x = n`. If `n` is a power of 3, then this expression will evaluate to an integer. If it's not a power of 3, it will be a non-integer number. So we just check if the result is equal to its integer value. If it is, then `n` is a power of 3, otherwise it's not.

